Falsifying or Inflating the Value of your 1031 Replacement Property</title><link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/1031podcast/~3/oGjhb4U6-vM/</link><category>1031 Blog</category><category>1031</category><category>1031 exchange</category><category>1031 tax exchange</category><category>falsifying</category><category>inflating</category><category>replacement property</category><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">info@1031podcast.com (Jeffery R. Peterson)</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2009 09:00:02 PDT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.1031podcast.com/?p=143</guid><content:encoded xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[<div class="media">
